<br>
1. Not everyone reads R &amp; F for various reasons.<br>
2. I wanted to have a <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> meaningful</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> and <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> intelligent</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> discussion about Ragefire <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> without</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> having to subject people to the vulgarity in R &amp; F.<br>
3. There are various forums for a reason. If I wanted to <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> rant</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> about Ragefire or the situation on Xev, I would have posted there.<br>
<br>
Now in response to some of the comments made since my last post:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Jalia, grats to you, I was just stating that the thread already existed.<br>
<br>
/points high horse<br>
/dismount <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I am not sure why you posted that. My response to your post was not meant to be in any shape or form an insult or give an air of superiority. It was giving you the reasons for my posting in the general forums. I would also like to say that your first post was not just a statement, but a veiled command to take my comments to a thread in which they did <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> belong. I repeat, my original post was <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> not</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> a rant or a flame.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I didn't post that in R&amp;F because I'm an &quot;idiot&quot;. I posted it there because on all message boards Ragefire topics end up in flames. It was a pre-emptive move on my part, nothing more. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I suppose it was wishful thinking on my part that there could be such thing as a meaningful debate about Ragefire, but I can see you are right. There are always a few who are not able to have thoughtful and thought-provoking posts which results in others responding to those, which snowballs an entire discussion into one giant flaming rant.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Some people don't want to have to wade to the sea of useless posts in R&amp;F to read/discuss something important to them. And some people can do so without resorting to flames.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I think they keyword there is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> some</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. And that, in my opinion, is sad.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I did not wish to have a Ranting and Flaming debate about Ragefire. I would much rather it be contained to intelligent debate rather than a string of swear words followed by Verant followed by more swear words followed by Ragefire.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
I couldn't agree more. Perhaps one day we can just have our own chat about the subject since it seems rather impossible here. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
It is so difficult to express meaning through text sometimes, which probably fuels flames more than anything. I would like to thank those who responded to this thread in a way that was intended. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Now it seems the original poster has fled and the post has degenerated into meaningless sewer sludge.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
